*DESCRIPTION_START
Seagulls are most often seen by landlubbers as freewheeling, shining shapes
of purest white, dancing in the winds that blow across the sandy beaches in
daylight. But they are also scavengers, omnivorous little beasties far
worse than any vulture, consuming dead, putrid fish and garbage. This
gull in particular has fed on the flesh of pirates, fed until it can no
longer fly, and this infusion of moral corruption has... changed it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
