MNUMBER 176
NAME zharkier
ADJECTIVE 119
*DESCRIPTION_START
Standing a mere two feet tall this horrid monstrosity created in the
infernal pits of Nygal'Ag inspires fear in all who gaze upon it. Made
from collected body parts, the Zharkier has been given life by foul
magic. Each individual part that makes up the creature has had the
skin flayed from it, leaving only the bloody organ or muscle itself
to pulse evilly in the light. A putrescent, sickly liquid forms a
protective coating around the organs and also drips continously from
the creature, creating small piles of a foul-smelling pus wherever it
walks. A sinewy spinal column, glowing with fiery red nerve endings
serves as the creatures tail, while a gaping hole in the creature's
throat emits glowing pustules of blood as the monster roars. A small
diamond pendant with a ruby in the center is imbedded into its chest,
and pulses occasionaly.
*DESCRIPTION_END
